it may be your classpath. often the xml classes a bundled together in many
different jars, like soap and junit. often these jars are &#39;sealed&#39; meaning
once you loaded a class from one jar, all other classes from this package
must be loaded from this jar.
you should order your classpath to have the xml package first, for example
classpath=jaxp.jar;xalan.jar;crimson.jar;soap.jar;junit.jar

